    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-18T15:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-18T15:36:00-05:00" n="586"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 612.119/1261</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-18T14:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>979. Plan outlined by Federal Reserve Board in your 981, April 17, 7 p.m., seems
                    desirable and feasible and meets with my approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
